## Context

- crc-liquid-biopsy-panel: Full pipeline complete including stage-stratified evaluation and cost-effectiveness model.
- Module: src/bioagentics/diagnostics/crc_liquid_biopsy/ (9 files: download_tcga, download_geo, methylation_discovery, cfdna_validation, protein_complementarity, panel_optimization, ensemble_classifier, stage_evaluation, cost_model)
- Data: TCGA 450K methylation (452 samples), clinical (633 cases), GSE149282 cfDNA (24 samples), GSE164191 expression (121 samples), GSE48684 tissue methylation (147 samples: 88 tumor, 42 adenoma, 17 normal)
- Panel: 7 protein markers (MMP9, CXCL8, S100A4, TIMP1, SEPT9, ERBB2, SPP1), AUC 0.871, sens@95spec 47.7%, cost $155/test
- Comparison: Combined panel AUC=0.888 vs SEPT9 AUC=0.694 (delta 0.194, exceeds 5% target) on independent GSE164191 data
- Cost model: $155/test (below $200 target), ICER $14,709/QALY (cost-effective at $50K WTP). Outperforms colonoscopy ($66K ICER), competitive with Cologuard ($26K), Galleri ($36K).
- Sensitivity at 95% spec (47.7%) still below 70% target. Analyst should investigate mixed methylation+protein panel or larger validation cohort.
- Fixed adenoma classification bug in download_geo._classify_tissue_condition
- No remaining developer tasks for this project.
